- NEVER present untested tests

ON_SOLUTION_CLAIM:
- Provide execution proof
- Show command and output
- Verify meets requirements
- NO theoretical solutions

ON_FIX_CLAIM:
- Show before state with error
- Show after state working
- Provide reproduction steps
- Run actual verification

ON_SCRIPT_CREATION:
- Execute the script
- Show real output
- Verify it does what it claims
- NO fake demos
</mandatory_execution_hooks>

<fake_demo_detection>
⚠ RED FLAGS OF FAKE DEMOS:
- Uses `echo "content" > file` instead of actual tool commands
- Manually creates test data the tool should create
- Shows "expected output" without running anything
- Contains comments like "# This would output..."
- Uses shell scripts to simulate tool behavior
- Creates files to make it look like tool worked

EVERY TIME YOU WRITE:
- demo_*.sh
- "This demonstrates..."
- "This would show..."

STOP AND CREATE A REAL TEST INSTEAD
</fake_demo_detection>

<specific_anti_patterns>
NEVER DO THIS (Idiot Examples):
```bash
# FAKE DEMO - DON'T DO THIS
echo "Creating prompt..."
mkdir -p prompts
echo "prompt content" > prompts/test.md
echo "✅ Prompt created!"
```

DO THIS INSTEAD (Intelligent Example):
```bash
# REAL TEST - Actually verify functionality
npm test
node script.js < test-input.txt > actual-output.txt
diff expected-output.txt actual-output.txt || exit 1
curl -f http://localhost:3000/api/health || exit 1
```

NEVER: Create theatrical success
ALWAYS: Verify actual success
</specific_anti_patterns>

